ON FEBRUARY 3, 2011, THE BOARD APPROVED A SHARE BUYBACK PROGRAM WHICH AUTHORIZED THE REPURCHASE OF UP TO 100 MILLION SHARES OF VERIZON COMMON STOCK TERMINATING NO LATER THAN THE CLOSE OF

BUSINESS ON FEBRUARY 28, 2014. THE BOARD ALSO DETERMINED THAT NO ADDITIONAL SHARES WERE TO BE PURCHASED UNDER THE PREVIOUSLY AUTHORIZED BUYBACK PROGRAM. THE PROGRAM PERMITS VERIZON TO REPURCHASE SHARES OVER TIME, WITH THE AMOUNT AND TIMING OF

REPURCHASES DEPENDING ON MARKET CONDITIONS AND CORPORATE NEEDS. THE BOARD MAY ALSO ENTER INTO RULE 10B5-1 PLANS FROM TIME TO TIME TO FACILITATE REPURCHASES OF ITS SHARES UNDER THIS AUTHORIZATION. A RULE 10B5-1 PLAN PERMITS THE COMPANY TO REPURCHASE

SHARES AT TIMES WHEN IT MIGHT OTHERWISE BE PREVENTED FROM DOING SO, PROVIDED THE PLAN IS ADOPTED WHEN THE COMPANY IS NOT AWARE OF MATERIAL NON-PUBLIC INFORMATION.

DURING THE FOURTH QUARTER OF 2010, VERIZON DID NOT REPURCHASE ANY SHARES OF VERIZON COMMON STOCK. AT DECEMBER 31, 2010, THE MAXIMUM NUMBER OF SHARES THAT COULD BE PURCHASED BY OR ON BEHALF OF VERIZON

UNDER THE SHARE BUYBACK PROGRAM IN PLACE AT THAT TIME WAS 60,015,938.

